article.headline: Milwaukee secures 88-80 win over Cleveland State
article.description: — Erik Pratt had 21 points in Milwaukee's 88-80 win over Cleveland State on Friday night.
article.linkText: Milwaukee secures 88-80 win over Cleveland State

video.headline: Milwaukee comes up clutch down the stretch to take down Cleveland State
video.caption: Milwaukee finds a few baskets late as they hold off Cleveland State for the 88-80 home win.

article.story: MILWAUKEE, Wisc. -- — Erik Pratt had 21 points in Milwaukee's 88-80 win over Cleveland State on Friday night. Pratt added six rebounds for the Panthers (9-8, 4-2 Horizon League). Elijah Jamison scored 20 points, going 6 of 10 from the floor, including 2 for 3 from 3-point range, and 6 for 8 from the line. BJ Freeman had 14 points and was 3 of 12 shooting, including 2 for 4 from 3-point range, and went 6 for 7 from the line. Tristan Enaruna led the way for the Vikings (11-7, 4-3) with 20 points, nine rebounds and five assists. Cleveland State also got 20 points and four blocks from Tevin Smith. Tujautae Williams also recorded 17 points. Up next for Milwaukee is a Thursday matchup with Northern Kentucky on the road, and Cleveland State visits Green Bay on Sunday. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
